# Copy to .env.local (gitignored, personal - never commit the real file) to test GitHub login
# and authenticated /api/* routes (Coach Chat included) on localhost via `vercel dev`.
#
# Without this, `npm run dev`/`vercel dev` bypass auth entirely (AuthContext.tsx's "local" mode) -
# fine for quick UI-only work, but means no real session cookie ever gets created, so any
# authenticated API call (repo data, sync trigger, Coach Chat) will 401 even with the server
# running. Setting this forces the real GitHub OAuth flow instead - see AuthContext.tsx's doc
# comment for the full explanation.
VITE_FORCE_HOSTED_AUTH=true
